            "answer_text": "Anywhere the Romans conquered. Slavery in ancient times was not based on colour etc. It was based on conquest, ergo you had Greek slaves as well as slaves form Gaul etc. Slavery was a way to pay your legionaries as slaves could be valuable. While the Romans had terrible laws for slave revolts ala Spartacus as the years past they often had slaves that became part of their households, scribes, etc. You\u2019ll notice in the plaster human remains if the cast has a leather belt around the waist that identifies a slave. Almost all gladiators were also slaves. ",
